docs.snippet: The Moustache Brothers carry on with a tradition of satire, but only to audiences of foreigners and not in public venues in Burmese....
docs.lead_paragraph: The Moustache Brothers carry on with a tradition of satire, but only to audiences of foreigners and not in public venues in Burmese.
docs.abstract: Myanmar comedy troupe Moustache Brothers joke about life under oppressive military rule, flaunting government law and risking imprisonment; group, founded by pro-democracy activist Par Par Lay, his brother U Lu Maw and cousin U Lu Zaw, performs to foreign audiences seven nights per week on makeshift stage inside garage of Mandalay home, ridiculing and defying their rulers.
